CMNFS00.text:
)ATTR
 + TYPE(TEXT) INTENS(LOW) SKIP(ON)
)BODY
%----------------------- PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE ------------------------
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
%ENTER/VERIFY PARAMETERS BELOW:
+
+ JOBNAME   %===>_CMNFSJNM+  The JOB NAME of job to be processed
+ JOBNUMBER %===>_Z    +     The JOB NUMBER of job to be processed (ie: 123)
+ OPTION    %===>_Z+        %S+-select;   %P+-print (submit batch);
+                           %L+-LIST ALL jobs with above JOBNAME
+
+ LIMIT(OPT)%===>_CMNFSLMT  +Date limit for "LIST" (MM MM/DD MM/DD/YYYY)
+
%ENTER OPTIONS FOR ONLINE/BATCH PRINTING BELOW:
+
+  DESTINATION%===>_CMNFSDST+ (ie: LOCAL RMT1 - Default = R0)
+  PRINT CLASS%===>_Z+        (ie: A Q - Defaults = A-online; *-batch)
+
%ENTER JOB CARD INFORMATION BELOW:
+
%===>_CMNBSVA                                                                 +
%===>_CMNBSVB                                                                 +
%===>_CMNBSVC                                                                 +
%===>_CMNBSVD                                                                 +
)INIT
  .HELP    = CMNFS00A
  .ZVARS='(CMNFSJNO CMNFSOPT CMNFSCLA)'
  IF (&CMNFSOPT = ' ')       /* DEFAULT IS LIST            */
      &CMNFSOPT = 'L'
)PROC
  &CMNFSWTR = 'SYS3.SOUTSYS'
)END

CMNFS00A.text:
%TUTORIAL --------------  PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE  --------------TUTORIAL
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
+This system is used to either:
+ 1) Retrieve a production jobs output from the DISKWTR's sysout datasets and
+    allow a user to browse that output online.
+or
+ 2) If the user does not want to wait for a sysout retrieval, submit a batch
+    job which will select the job for printing.
+
% To use this panel , you must:
+
+    1. Enter%JOBNAME+ -  use an entire jobname for the%P+- print, or%S+- select
+                         option. The entire jobname can also be used for the
+                         list option or a generic name can be used. A generic
+                         name consists of one or more characters followed by
+                         an asterisk. (ie: &ZUSER.*  TM*  pmsds*)
+
+    2. Enter%JOB NUMBER+- The job number is used if a specified job is needed.
+                          If the job number is not used, last job run matching
+                          the jobname is selected. Job number is not used when
+                          the%L+- list option is used.
+                          (Do not use a "J" in the job number)
+ Hit%ENTER+to obtain next help panel
)INIT
   &ZCONT = CMNFS00B
)END

CMNFS00B.text:
%TUTORIAL ------ -------  PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE  --------------TUTORIAL
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
+   3) Enter%OPTION+-%P+- a) print the job listing if you just finished browsing
+                         b) submit a batch job which will print the job listing
+                    %S+- select a job for an%ONLINE+ browse of the job listing
+                    %L+- build a table of all the jobs in the jobname field
+                         and allow a user to select or print from that table
+
+   4) Enter%DATE LIMIT+- this is valid only when using the%List+option. This
+                         will limit the size of the table based on the number
+                         of days that a user wants to back up.
+                         The default is three(3) days back.
+
+
+
+ Hit%ENTER+to obtain next help panel
)INIT
   &ZCONT = CMNFS00C
)END

CMNFS00C.text:
%TUTORIAL ------ -------  PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE  --------------TUTORIAL
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
+   5) Enter%DESTINATION+- this is used to route the output to a specified
+                          printer destination. It is needed when you use
+                          the%Select+OR%Print+ options.
+                          Appropriate defaults are taken for you.
+
+   6) Enter%PRINT CLASS+- this is used to print the output in a specified
+                          printer class. It is needed when you use the
+                          %Select+OR%Print+ options.
+                          Appropriate defaults are taken for you.
+
+   7) Enter%JOB CARD+-   this is used when the%Print+option is used. Verify
+                         the job card information before submitting a batch
+                         print.
+
+
)INIT
   &ZCONT = CMNFS00C
)END

CMNFS00D.text:
%TUTORIAL ------ -------  PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE  --------------TUTORIAL
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
+ This is the table of jobs which was built when the%List+option was selected.
+ You can now select any of the jobs on this table by entering one of the
+ following options at the left of a required job:
+   %P+- a) print the job listing if you just finished browsing
+        b) submit a batch job which will print the job listing
+   %S+- select a job for an%ONLINE+ browse of the job listing
+   %Q+- query the dataset name where the sysout listing exists
+
+ The following is an explanation of the fields in the table:
% note: DATE/TIME/DAY are created when the job is written to the DISKWTR system
%       and may not always match the times when the job was run.
+
% JOBNAME   +- name of the job requested (or generic portion of the name)
% JOB NUMBER+- jes job number created when job was submitted
% DATE      +- date the job was written to the DISKWTR system
% TIME      +- time the job was written to the DISKWTR system
% DAY       +- day of the week the job was written to the DISKWTR system
% LINES     +- number of lines in the job listing
+              (will contain ??? if the job is on the ACTIVE DISKWTR file)
% DEVICE    +- device type where the output is held (will be TAPE or ONLINE)
)INIT
  &ZCONT  = CMNFS00A
)END

CMNFS00E.text:
%TUTORIAL ------ -------  PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE  --------------TUTORIAL
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
+ A job listing was selected for online browse and the listing was on a%TAPE+.
+ This required a tape mount and tied up a terminal for a long running option.
+ you are now forced to reply if this job is to be printed. If you reply%YES+,
+ the job listing will be printed and thus another tape mount will be avoided.
+ If you reply%NO+ the job will not be printed, but if you later decide to print
+ it another tape mount will be required.
+
)INIT
  &ZCONT  = CMNFS00A
)END

CMNFS01.text:
)ATTR
 @ TYPE(OUTPUT) INTENS(LOW)
 _ TYPE(INPUT) INTENS(HIGH)
 + TYPE(TEXT) INTENS(LOW) SKIP(ON)
)BODY
%----------------------- PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE ------------------------
+
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD                                            %SCROLL ===>_AMT +
+
+   VALID OPTIONS BELOW: %S+- select for online browse
+                        %P+- print - (print after select or submit batch job)
+
%OPT  JOBNAME      JOB #       DATE        TIME     DAY     LINES     DEVICE
% -   --------   --------   ----------   --------   ---   ---------   ------
)MODEL
 _Z+ @Z         @Z         @Z           @Z         @Z    @Z          @Z
)INIT
 .HELP    = CMNFS00D
 .ZVARS='(CMNFSSEL CMNFSNAM CMNFSJNU CMNFSDAT CMNFSTIM CMNFSDAY +
 CMNFSLIN CMNFSDEV)'
 &AMT = 'PAGE'
)END

CMNFS02.text:
%------------------ PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE -----------------------------
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
+
%ENTER/VERIFY PARAMETERS BELOW:
+
+
+                   OPTION TO PRINT%===>_CMNFSYNO+
+
+                   (YES OR NO; Y OR N)
)INIT
  .HELP = CMNFS00E
)END

CMNFS03.text:
%------------------ PRODUCTION BATCH SYSOUT BROWSE -----------------------------
%COMMAND ===>_ZCMD
%
+
% DISK WRITER DATASET NAMES:
+
+
+    JOURNAL DATASET     =>%&CMNFSJDS
+
+
+    SYSOUT DATA DATASET =>%&CMNFSDSN
+
)END
